­<em>Zombie Panic! Source ­HOWTO</em>­­
<br />
<br /><strong>Installation:</strong>­­
<br />­
<br />
Run `wine steam -applaunch 17500` to invoke the installation. 
<br />
<br /><strong>Issues:</strong>
<br />
<br />
A tricky font <a href="http://bugs.winehq.org/show_bug.cgi?id=7698">bug</a> can cause Source games to crash sporadically. Use winecfg to set the Windows version to "Windows 98" for the hl2.exe executable.
<br />
<br />
Due to a <a href="http://bugs.winehq.org/show_bug.cgi?id=12453">bug</a> in wine, the default Direct3D 9 renderer of most Source engine games will perform badly. You will want to use Direct3D 8; right click on the Zombie Panic! Source game in Steam, click properties, and add -dxlevel 81 to the launch options. Start the game, quit, and remove the launch option.

